{% doc %}
  @prompt
    Create a fully responsive slider module for a Shopify store with up to 5 slides. Each slide should include:
    
    Headline & Sub-headline: editable text with adjustable font weight, size, color, and alignment.
    
    Button: editable label, link, padding, border radius/width, hover styles.
    
    Background image: upload/select with controls for object-fit (cover/contain), focal point picker, position (X/Y), repeat/no-repeat, and optional parallax.
    
    Foreground image/graphic: upload/select with full adjustment controls:
    
    Resize (px / %)
    
    Position (X/Y, anchors, custom offsets)
    
    Alignment (left, center, right; top, middle, bottom)
    
    Rotation, flip (H/V), opacity, blend mode
    
    Z-index (layer ordering)
    
    Mobile-specific behavior
    
    On mobile view, the foreground image must automatically:
    
    Display below the content block (headline, sub-headline, button).
    
    Fit the full available width (100% responsive width).
    
    Maintain aspect ratio to avoid distortion.
    
    Layout & Positioning
    
    Draggable Content Box with per-breakpoint controls (desktop/tablet/mobile) for text size, spacing, and alignment.
    
    Snap-to grid, margin/padding controls, and layering manager.
    
    Navigation
    
    Arrows and dots. Dots fully customizable: size, spacing, shape (circle/square/pill), fill color, hover/active color, border (width, style, radius, color), and position (bottom/left/right/custom offsets).
    
    Behavior
    
    Transition styles (slide/fade), autoplay toggle & speed, pause on hover, loop, swipe, keyboard nav.
    
    Editor UX
    
    All settings adjustable in Shopify theme editor (no code).
    
    Sortable slide list with per-slide overrides.
    
    Accessibility & Performance
    
    Alt text for all images, ARIA labels, focus states.
    
    Lazy-load images, responsive CSS, mobile-first design.
    
    Deliver as an Online Store 2.0 section with JSON schema + Liquid/HTML/CSS/JS, clean and well-commented code., the background ain't working

